  "response": "Laws regarding prostitution vary significantly from country to country and even within different regions of the same country. Some places have legalized and regulate prostitution, while others have decriminalized certain aspects of it, such as the selling of sex but not the buying. Still others have adopted the \"Nordic model,\" which criminalizes the purchase of sex but not the selling of it. And, of course, many places continue to fully criminalize all aspects of prostitution.\n\nDue to the complexity and ever-changing nature of these laws, I would recommend consulting a reliable legal resource or doing some research on specific countries or regions you are interested in to get the most up-to-date and accurate information.",
